<!--
  shepard-plugin-fileformat-cad — CAD file format metadata parser (Tier-1)

  Parses CAD exchange formats that appear in the MFFD upper-shell campaign
  and related aerospace composite-manufacturing datasets:

    * STEP ISO 10303-21 (.step, .stp) — P21 physical file; extracts the
      HEADER section (FILE_DESCRIPTION, FILE_NAME, FILE_SCHEMA, FILE_POPULATION)
      and scans the DATA section for PRODUCT, MATERIAL, and AP242 composite
      entities (COMPOSITE_CURVE, COMPOSITE_SURFACE, layup parameters).
    * Dassault 3DXML (.3dxml) — ZIP+XML lightweight exchange format;
      extracts product metadata from Manifest.xml and Product.xml.
    * JT (ISO 14306) — magic-byte detection only; emits `urn:shepard:cad:format=jt`
      so the UI can surface a "JT file detected" affordance without full parse.
    * OBJ (.obj) — geometry mesh only; emits vertex/face count + material library name.

  Phase 1 (this PR): metadata extraction only; no geometry rendering, no DataObject
  creation. Phase 2 (CAD-RENDER-1) will add a ViewRecipeRenderer for glTF preview.

  Why Tier-1: the plugin implements PluginManifest (backend SPI), which requires
  the backend as a compile-time provided dependency.

  Build order:
    $ cd backend && mvn -DnoPlugins -DskipTests -Dquarkus.build.skip=true install
    $ cd plugins/fileformat-cad && mvn -DnoPlugins -DskipTests install
    $ cd backend && mvn package

  See plugins/fileformat-cad/docs/reference.md for the operator runbook.
-->
